{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/431", "repo": "rails", "body": "@josevalim: Good point. The <tt>request.put?</tt> check is a valid breakage that will cause problems. We could have <tt>request.put?</tt> return <tt>true</tt> for more robust backwards compatibility, but I don't think it's worth it.\r\n\r\n\"form helpers should only use PATCH...\" was not to say that PATCH usage will be uncommon, but that it would be limited to routes in the app. This was a response to \"Remember, those forms also post to routes which aren't generated by the resources helper, so changing the verb will break applications.\"", "_id": {"$oid": "52386048bd3543c15101224e"}, "issue_id": 431, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1126665", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/431#issuecomment-1126665", "updated_at": "2011-05-09T22:07:39Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee", "login": "dlee", "gravatar_id": "139de3f8c3d6ee008cdb3abd3da23908", "html_url": "https://github.com/dlee", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/139de3f8c3d6ee008cdb3abd3da23908?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F80177fe965b78111f4dfee80cfdc3689.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 7035, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/dlee/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-05-09T22:07:39Z", "id": 1126665, "owner": "rails"}
